Here's a summary of everything that changed in `pipeline_refactored.py`:

---

**Refactoring — original problems fixed:**

| Problem | Fix |
|---|---|
| Hardcoded credentials & paths (`DB_PATH`, `LOG_FILE`, `DB_HOST` etc.) | All config moved to `Config` dataclass loaded from env vars (`DB_PATH`, `LOG_FILE`, `DB_HOST`, `DB_PORT`, `DB_USER`) with sensible defaults |
| SQL injection (string `%` formatting) | All DB writes use `?` parameterized queries via `conn.execute()` / `conn.executemany()` |
| 121-line monolith in `proc_data()` | Split into `extract_logs()` → `transform()` → `load_to_db()` + `generate_report()` with private helpers |
| Fragile `line.split(" ")` parsing | 4 named capture-group regex patterns (`_RE_ERROR`, `_RE_USER`, `_RE_API`, `_RE_WARN`) |
| No type hints or docs | Full type hints and docstrings on all public functions, dataclasses (`Config`, `LogEntry`, `AggregatedMetrics`, `SessionTracker`) |
| `open()` without context manager | All file I/O uses `with` / `Path().open()` context managers |
| XSS in HTML (raw message interpolation) | Messages escaped with `html.escape()` |
| Dead credential variables printed but never used | Kept as status message for backward compat; `DB_PASS` removed entirely |
| Variable `d_list`/`r`/`endpoint_stats` with cryptic names | Replaced with typed dataclasses: `LogEntry`, `AggregatedMetrics` |

**Output verified:** `report.html` and `metrics.db` contain identical data to the original. The entry-point (`run_pipeline()`) can also accept a `Config` object for testing without env vars.
